				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In performed music, you need to transpose a piece to fit the optimal range of instruments used.</div><br />As a player you don't need to transpose anything - the arranger does. You play your music sheet as the aranger decided to. That's what a PAL NES is supposed to do - if the game says &quot;I want to play an A note&quot; then it should play an A note, not a G note.<br /><br />I see rainwarrior's point in that by adjusting the pitch table it can still sound a little different than the NTSC original - however by not transposing it it will also sound different due to lower pitch, so it's a matter of preference. Guaranteeing music to sound 100% identical across versions is basically impossible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

